# shadcn/ui Documentation Overview

## What is shadcn/ui?

shadcn/ui is a collection of beautifully-designed, accessible components built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Radix UI. The platform emphasizes Open Code, Composition, Distribution and supports multiple frameworks including Next.js, Vite, Remix, and Astro.

## Key Features

- **CLI Tool**: Automates component installation and management
- **Registry System**: Enables publishing and distributing code
- **Multi-Framework Support**: Works across various JavaScript frameworks
- **Theming System**: Allows customization of colors and design tokens
- **AI Integration**: Includes an MCP Server for AI assistant integration

## Component Categories

The documentation organizes 70+ components into functional groups:

- **Form & Input**: 17 components for building interactive forms
- **Layout & Navigation**: 8 structural components
- **Overlays & Dialogs**: 11 modal and popup components
- **Feedback & Status**: 7 notification elements
- **Display & Media**: 10 content presentation components
- **Miscellaneous**: 4 utility components

## Important Rules

- NEVER try to create a Shadcn component yourself, it must always come through the command line
- NEVER modify the actual component once imported, use classNames to modify an imported component instead
- Always use the Shadcn MCP server to identify which components are available and how to install them
